#eNCA #DStv403 DURBAN - The KwaZulu-Natal government says it's ready to deal with more heavy rains this weekend. KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala says disaster management protocols are in place but he says those in low-lying areas must be ready to leave if the risk of flooding arises. READ: Water, power outages in Durban Ziklalala was providing updates on the mop-up operations in the province.